dataIdInfo.idAbs: METRORail Lines was created using METMap, METRO's street centerline map is a version of Star*Map as created and maintained by the Geographic Data Committee of the Houston-Galveston Area Council. The METRORail Lines were created as a centerline between the existing tracks as shown on January 2014 Aerial Photography. METRORail Red line is currently operating. The Purple and Green Lines are scheduled to be in operation in May 2015. The Green Line will initially operate only to Altic /Howward Hughes Station. Upon completion of the overpass over the frieght railroad just east of Altic/Howard Hughes Station, the Green Line will operate fully to Magnolia Park Station.
